    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Student s)
      Compares parameter Student object s to caller and returns -1, 0, or 1 depending on whether the caller is less than s, equal to s, or greater than s, respectively. Order is determined first by alphabetical order of the Student's last names, then by first name, and lastly by their unity id's. Alphabetical ordering is implemented through use of the imported SortedList java library.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Student>
      Parameters:
      s - Student object being compared to the caller.
      Returns:
      Integer value determining the ordering of the two objects.
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the parameter object s is null.
      ClassCastException - if the parameter is not a student object.
